emory studies the work offers multiple theoretical and methodological approaches for everyone interested in the heritage of audiovisual media: film and media scholars, memory scholars, historians, art historians, social scientists, librarians or archivists, curators and festival programmers alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2019) 0aCollective memory. 0aDocumentary filmsxSocial aspects. 0aMass media and culture. 0aMass mediaxSocial aspects. 4aTranscultural memory. 4aarchive. 4afilm. 4aremediation. 70(DE-601)1048144890(DE-588)4012653-5aDokumentarfilm2gnd 70(DE-601)1051709250(DE-588)4200793-8aKollektives Gedächtnis2gnd 70(DE-601)1062350790(DE-588)4037877-9aMassenmedien2gnd 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2015z9783110438673oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831104345210 cprintz978311043762140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110436372423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110436372.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aZDB-23-DGGb2015  aZDB-23-DKUb2015